      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;exploring-integer-overflow-libxml2-integer-overflow-oob&#34;&gt;Exploring Integer Overflow: libxml2 Integer Overflow OOB&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In everyday life, numbers feel endless. You can always count one higher, or subtract one more. But computers donâ€™t work like that. Inside your machine, numbers are stored in &lt;strong&gt;fixed-sized containers&lt;/strong&gt;  and when you push them past their limits, strange things happen. When a calculation produces a value thatâ€™s too large or too small for its container, we get integer overflow or integer underflow.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
